20  x86Specifications::x86Specifications(triton::arch::architecture_e arch) {
21  if (arch != triton::arch::ARCH_X86 && arch != triton::arch::ARCH_X86_64)
22  throw triton::exceptions::Architecture("x86Specifications::x86Specifications(): Invalid architecture.");
23 
24  if (arch == triton::arch::ARCH_X86_64) {
25  // Fill id2reg and name2id with those available in X86_64 from spec
26  #define REG_SPEC(UPPER_NAME, LOWER_NAME, X86_64_UPPER, X86_64_LOWER, X86_64_PARENT, X86_UPPER, X86_LOWER, X86_PARENT, X86_AVAIL) \
27  id2reg.emplace(ID_REG_X86_##UPPER_NAME, \
28  triton::arch::Register(triton::arch::ID_REG_X86_##UPPER_NAME, \
29  #LOWER_NAME, \
30  triton::arch::ID_REG_X86_##X86_64_PARENT, \
31  X86_64_UPPER, \
32  X86_64_LOWER, \
33  true) \
34  ); \
35  name2id.emplace(#LOWER_NAME, ID_REG_X86_##UPPER_NAME);
36  // Handle register not available in capstone as normal registers
37  #define REG_SPEC_NO_CAPSTONE REG_SPEC
38  #include "triton/x86.spec"
39  }
40  else {
41  assert(arch == triton::arch::ARCH_X86);
42  // Fill id2reg and name2id with those available in X86 from spec
43  #define REG_SPEC(UPPER_NAME, LOWER_NAME, _1, _2, _3, X86_UPPER, X86_LOWER, X86_PARENT, X86_AVAIL) \
44  if (X86_AVAIL) \
45  id2reg.emplace(ID_REG_X86_##UPPER_NAME, \
46  triton::arch::Register(triton::arch::ID_REG_X86_##UPPER_NAME, \
47  #LOWER_NAME, \
48  triton::arch::ID_REG_X86_##X86_PARENT, \
49  X86_UPPER, \
50  X86_LOWER, \
51  true) \
52  ); \
53  name2id.emplace(#LOWER_NAME, ID_REG_X86_##UPPER_NAME);
54  // Handle register not available in capstone as normal registers
55  #define REG_SPEC_NO_CAPSTONE REG_SPEC
56  #include "triton/x86.spec"
57  }
58  }
59 
60 
61  triton::arch::register_e x86Specifications::capstoneRegisterToTritonRegister(triton::uint32 id) const {
62  triton::arch::register_e tritonId = triton::arch::ID_REG_INVALID;
63 
64  switch (id) {
65  // Convert registers from capstone value to triton value
66  #define REG_SPEC(UPPER_NAME, _1, _2, _3, _4, _5, _6, _7, _8) \
67  case triton::extlibs::capstone::X86_REG_##UPPER_NAME: \
68  tritonId = triton::arch::ID_REG_X86_##UPPER_NAME; \
69  break;
70  // Ignore registers not available in capstone
71  #define REG_SPEC_NO_CAPSTONE(_1, _2, _3, _4, _5, _6, _7, _8, _9)
72  #include "triton/x86.spec"
73 
74  default:
75  tritonId = triton::arch::ID_REG_INVALID;
76  break;
77 
78  }
79  return tritonId;
80  }

5280  break;
5281
